To derive the exploitation command, a systematic code analysis and testing process is followed:
  ### 1. Identifying the Constraints

  By examining the project files, we identify two conflicting rules:

  •  nginx.conf : The line  client_max_body_size 75;  limits the HTTP request body to 75 bytes.
  •  index.mjs : The line  if (string.length < 1000)  requires the input string length to be at least 1000 characters.

  Since 1000 characters of text exceed 75 bytes, a standard string input is impossible to transmit. This indicates we must pass an object that bypasses the length
  check.
